      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GEM N EM NZ (9) is a newcomer to the David Micallef yard from NZ. Last seen when winning over 2000m at Motukarara last month. Should enjoy a pretty soft run from this draw, with the sprint lane in play a big role. Can kick off on this side of the Tasman with a win. ULTIMATE COOKIE (2) has been racing well of late. Placed two back at Parkes before a solid fifth at her latest appearance from the back row at Penrith, beaten 7.6 metres. Should enjoy an economical run from this draw. GET UP BETTY (1) has been coming from wider or second row barriers so should enjoy the ace draw. LAST FLITE (3) has put together a string of top-four finishes, winning from this barrier two back and placing from the second line last start. Respect.",
